 \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/\\u00c9dith_Piaf\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/\\u00c9dith_Piaf\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The crowd\", \"from\": 238, \"to\": 247}, {\"ngram\": \"the closing stages\", \"from\": 269, \"to\": 287}, {\"ngram\": \"the sound\", \"from\": 291, \"to\": 300}, {\"ngram\": \"this prolific partnership\", \"from\": 319, \"to\": 344}, {\"ngram\": \"nothing\", \"from\": 350, \"to\": 357}, {\"ngram\": \"theOlympic dressagearena\", \"from\": 371, \"to\": 395}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The world number ones and reigning European Champions arrived in Paris unbeaten in their last 35 international outings - a winning streak that started when they claimed individual gold in Tokyo.\", \"from\": 400, \"to\": 594, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 465, \"end\": 470, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.1713880012633365e-17, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}, {\"begin\": 588, \"end\": 593, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\", \"score\": 0.9968842363986326, \"rank\": 0.003125478823036211, \"text\": \"Tokyo\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The world number ones\", \"from\": 400, \"to\": 421}, {\"ngram\": \"European Champions\", \"from\": 435, \"to\": 453}, {\"ngram\": \"their last 35 international outings\", \"from\": 483, \"to\": 518}, {\"ngram\": \"individual gold\", \"from\": 569, \"to\": 584}]}, {\"sentence\": \"They leave as only the fourth combination to ever defend an Olympic individual dressage gold medal, landing victory on 90.09% and the only combination to break the 90% barrier at these Games.\", \"from\": 595, \"to\": 786, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"only the fourth combination\", \"from\": 609, \"to\": 636}, {\"ngram\": \"an Olympic individual dressage gold medal\", \"from\": 652, \"to\": 693}, {\"ngram\": \"victory\", \"from\": 703, \"to\": 710}, {\"ngram\": \"90.09%\", \"from\": 714, \"to\": 720}, {\"ngram\": \"the 90% barrier\", \"from\": 755, \"to\": 770}, {\"ngram\": \"these Games\", \"from\": 774, \"to\": 785}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"She knows everything.\", \"from\": 788, \"to\": 810, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"everything\", \"from\": 799, \"to\": 809}]}, {\"sentence\": \"She's the most intelligent horse I have ever had,\\\" said an emotional Jessica, who rides this 17-year-old doyenne for B\\u00e9atrice A. Buerchler-Keller and Micaela Werndl.\", \"from\": 811, \"to\": 976, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 880, \"end\": 887, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jessica_Buchanan\", \"score\": 0.9999953895500637, \"rank\": 4.610471174996568e-06, \"text\": \"Jessica\", \"types\": [\"Q95074\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jessica_Buchanan\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jessica_Buchanan\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the most intelligent horse\", \"from\": 817, \"to\": 843}, {\"ngram\": \"this 17-year-old doyenne\", \"from\": 899, \"to\": 923}, {\"ngram\": \"B\\u00e9atrice A. Buerchler\", \"from\": 928, \"to\": 949}, {\"ngram\": \"Keller\", \"from\": 950, \"to\": 956}, {\"ngram\": \"Micaela Werndl\", \"from\": 961, \"to\": 975}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"She was 1000% with me.\", \"from\": 978, \"to\": 1001, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"1000%\", \"from\": 987, \"to\": 992}]}, {\"sentence\": \"She had no ear or eye anywhere else than me.\", \"from\": 1002, \"to\": 1046, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"no ear\", \"from\": 1010, \"to\": 1016}, {\"ngram\": \"eye\", \"from\": 1020, \"to\": 1023}]}, {\"sentence\": \"She was listening so carefully and she really showed me that that's what she wants to do.\", \"from\": 1047, \"to\": 1136, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"This is why it makes me so emotional because I do not know if I will ever get a horse like her\\u2026 she is out of this world.\\\"\", \"from\": 1137, \"to\": 1259, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a horse\", \"from\": 1215, \"to\": 1222}, {\"ngram\": \"this world\", \"from\": 1247, \"to\": 1257}]}, {\"sentence\": \"As they exited the arena after their test, Jessica wiped a tear from her eye.\", \"from\": 1263, \"to\": 1340, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1306, \"end\": 1313, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jessica_Buchanan\", \"score\": 0.9999953895500637, \"rank\": 4.610471174996568e-06, \"text\": \"Jessica\", \"types\": [\"Q95074\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jessica_Buchanan\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jessica_Buchanan\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the arena\", \"from\": 1278, \"to\": 1287}, {\"ngram\": \"their test\", \"from\": 1294, \"to\": 1304}, {\"ngram\": \"a tear\", \"from\": 1320, \"to\": 1326}, {\"ngram\": \"her eye\", \"from\": 1332, \"to\": 1339}]}, {\"sentence\": \"By the time she stepped onto the podium to receive her Olympic dressage gold medal, the tears were flowing freely.\", \"from\": 1341, \"to\": 1455, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the time\", \"from\": 1344, \"to\": 1352}, {\"ngram\": \"the podium\", \"from\": 1370, \"to\": 1380}, {\"ngram\": \"her Olympic dressage gold medal\", \"from\": 1392, \"to\": 1423}, {\"ngram\": \"the tears\", \"from\": 1425, \"to\": 1434}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"I am overwhelmed and exhausted.\", \"from\": 1457, \"to\": 1489, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"I had to cry too much today,\\\" said Jessica, reflecting on the difference she felt performing today as an individual compared to the pressure of riding as team anchor yesterday.\", \"from\": 1490, \"to\": 1666, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1525, \"end\": 1532, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jessica_Buchanan\", \"score\": 0.9999953895500637, \"rank\": 4.610471174996568e-06, \"text\": \"Jessica\", \"types\": [\"Q95074\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jessica_Buchanan\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jessica_Buchanan\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the difference\", \"from\": 1548, \"to\": 1562}, {\"ngram\": \"an individual\", \"from\": 1592, \"to\": 1605}, {\"ngram\": \"the pressure\", \"from\": 1618, \"to\": 1630}, {\"ngram\": \"riding\", \"from\": 1634, \"to\": 1640}, {\"ngram\": \"team anchor\", \"from\": 1644, \"to\": 1655}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"Today I woke up and I thought, 'it's all about trust'.\", \"from\": 1668, \"to\": 1723, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"trust\", \"from\": 1716, \"to\": 1721}]}, {\"sentence\": \"We are enough.\", \"from\": 1724, \"to\": 1738, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"I can trust myself.\", \"from\": 1739, \"to\": 1758, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"I can trust Dalera, I can trust us and it's about letting go.\", \"from\": 1759, \"to\": 1820, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Dalera\", \"from\": 1771, \"to\": 1777}, {\"ngram\": \"us\", \"from\": 1791, \"to\": 1793}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"This was a mental game change from yesterday to today.\", \"from\": 1822, \"to\": 1877, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a mental game change\", \"from\": 1832, \"to\": 1852}, {\"ngram\": \"yesterday\", \"from\": 1858, \"to\": 1867}, {\"ngram\": \"today\", \"from\": 1871, \"to\": 1876}]}, {\"sentence\": \"I did not change anything about the equipment, or about Dalera - about anything.\\\"\", \"from\": 1878, \"to\": 1959, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"anything\", \"from\": 1895, \"to\": 1903}, {\"ngram\": \"the equipment\", \"from\": 1910, \"to\": 1923}, {\"ngram\": \"Dalera\", \"from\": 1934, \"to\": 1940}, {\"ngram\": \"anything\", \"from\": 1949, \"to\": 1957}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Tapping her own head, she added: \\\"It was just in here [I needed] to let go, to trust and to tell her that she is enough.\\\"\", \"from\": 1961, \"to\": 2082, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"her own head\", \"from\": 1969, \"to\": 1981}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Jessica spent the time she was pregnant with her daughter to create this freestyle.\", \"from\": 2084, \"to\": 2167, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2084, \"end\": 2091, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jessica_Buchanan\", \"score\": 0.9999953895500637, \"rank\": 4.610471174996568e-06, \"text\": \"Jessica\", \"types\": [\"Q95074\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jessica_Buchanan\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jessica_Buchanan\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the time\", \"from\": 2098, \"to\": 2106}, {\"ngram\": \"her daughter\", \"from\": 2129, \"to\": 2141}, {\"ngram\": \"this freestyle\", \"from\": 2152, \"to\": 2166}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"I was six weeks pregnant and listening to 'Non, Je ne regrette rien' walking on the beach in Spain with my husband.\", \"from\": 2169, \"to\": 2285, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2263, \"end\": 2268, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Spain\", \"score\": 0.9848626176158343, \"rank\": 0.014131489624868484, \"text\": \"Spain\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Spain\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Spain\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"'Non, Je ne regrette rien\", \"from\": 2212, \"to\": 2237}, {\"ngram\": \"the beach\", \"from\": 2250, \"to\": 2259}, {\"ngram\": \"my husband\", \"from\": 2274, \"to\": 2284}]}, {\"sentence\": \"I got goosebumps on my whole body and told him, 'this is the music - this is what I want to do',\\\" she said.\", \"from\": 2286, \"to\": 2393, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"goosebumps\", \"from\": 2292, \"to\": 2302}, {\"ngram\": \"my whole body\", \"from\": 2306, \"to\": 2319}, {\"ngram\": \"the music\", \"from\": 2343, \"to\": 2352}]}, {\"sentence\": \"This pair's bond has blossomed over the nine years they have spent together - Jessica has even been napping in the mare's stable here in Paris.\", \"from\": 2395, \"to\": 2538, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2473, \"end\": 2480, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jessica_Buchanan\", \"score\": 0.9999953895500637, \"rank\": 4.610471174996568e-06, \"text\": \"Jessica\", \"types\": [\"Q95074\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jessica_Buchanan\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jessica_Buchanan\"}, {\"begin\": 2532, \"end\": 2537, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.1713880012633365e-17, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"This pair's bond\", \"from\": 2395, \"to\": 2411}, {\"ngram\": \"the nine years\", \"from\": 2431, \"to\": 2445}]}, {\"sentence\": \"It's a bond Jessica puts down to listening to the mare and being led by what the horse tells her.\", \"from\": 2539, \"to\": 2636, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a bond\", \"from\": 2544, \"to\": 2550}, {\"ngram\": \"Jessica\", \"from\": 2551, \"to\": 2558}, {\"ngram\": \"the mare\", \"from\": 2585, \"to\": 2593}, {\"ngram\": \"the horse\", \"from\": 2616, \"to\": 2625}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"She tells me how long she wants to hack out or she tells me when she needs a canter - a wild canter on the galloping track - and she tells me when she wants to work.\", \"from\": 2638, \"to\": 2804, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a canter\", \"from\": 2714, \"to\": 2722}, {\"ngram\": \"a wild canter\", \"from\": 2725, \"to\": 2738}, {\"ngram\": \"the galloping track\", \"from\": 2742, \"to\": 2761}]}, {\"sentence\": \"She is just too good for everyone,\\\" she said.\", \"from\": 2805, \"to\": 2850, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"everyone\", \"from\": 2830, \"to\": 2838}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"She's so smart and so funny.\", \"from\": 2852, \"to\": 2881, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"I wanted to sleep in the hammock today and she was just playing with me - she was so funny, cheeky and happy.\\\"\", \"from\": 2882, \"to\": 2992, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the hammock\", \"from\": 2903, \"to\": 2914}]}, {\"sentence\": \"She added: \\\"She knew today was the day and she just did it.\", \"from\": 2994, \"to\": 3053, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the day\", \"from\": 3025, \"to\": 3032}]}, {\"sentence\": \"I have not enough time yet [to fully thank her], but I will continue to just thank her again and again and again, and kiss her and cuddle her.\", \"from\": 3054, \"to\": 3196, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"not enough time\", \"from\": 3061, \"to\": 3076}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"I know that my husband, Franzi [my show groom], and the owner is with her and they will all just tell her that she's just amazing.\", \"from\": 3198, \"to\": 3329, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3223, \"end\": 3229, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Franzi\", \"score\": 0.9999999941114766, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Franzi\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Franzi\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Franzi\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"my show groom\", \"from\": 3231, \"to\": 3244}, {\"ngram\": \"the owner\", \"from\": 3251, \"to\": 3260}]}, {\"sentence\": \"I will spoil her to the last day of her life.\\\"\", \"from\": 3330, \"to\": 3376, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the last day\", \"from\": 3350, \"to\": 3362}, {\"ngram\": \"her life\", \"from\": 3366, \"to\": 3374}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Their closest rival wasIsabell Werth, the world's most decorated Olympian, who re-wrote the lyrics ofMandyto \\\"Oh, Wendy\\\", in honour of her exceptional new ride.They scored 89.61% to put the pressure onthe remaining competitors.\", \"from\": 3378, \"to\": 3605, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3443, \"end\": 3451, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympic_Games\", \"score\": 0.9999999055385205, \"rank\": 9.445500914049259e-08, \"text\": \"Olympian\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympic_Games\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympic_Games\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Their closest rival wasIsabell Werth\", \"from\": 3378, \"to\": 3414}, {\"ngram\": \"the lyrics\", \"from\": 3466, \"to\": 3476}, {\"ngram\": \"\\\"Oh, Wendy\", \"from\": 3487, \"to\": 3497}, {\"ngram\": \"honour\", \"from\": 3503, \"to\": 3509}, {\"ngram\": \"her exceptional new ride\", \"from\": 3513, \"to\": 3537}, {\"ngram\": \"the pressure\", \"from\": 3564, \"to\": 3576}, {\"ngram\": \"onthe remaining competitors\", \"from\": 3577, \"to\": 3604}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Britain's world championsLottie Fry and Glamourdale sealed bronzein this gripping finale to the Olympic dressage, with a score of 88.97%.\", \"from\": 3607, \"to\": 3744, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3607, \"end\": 3614, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\", \"score\": 0.9996498087175152, \"rank\": 0.000350096965134803, \"text\": \"Britain\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Glamourdale\", \"from\": 3647, \"to\": 3658}, {\"ngram\": \"bronzein\", \"from\": 3666, \"to\": 3674}, {\"ngram\": \"this gripping finale\", \"from\": 3675, \"to\": 3695}, {\"ngram\": \"the Olympic dressage\", \"from\": 3699, \"to\": 3719}, {\"ngram\": \"a score\", \"from\": 3726, \"to\": 3733}, {\"ngram\": \"88.97%\", \"from\": 3737, \"to\": 3743}]}, {\"sentence\": \"You might also be interested in: Stay in touch wit